\frac{43}{6} & \frac{5}{3} - x \\
\end{array}
\right)$$

Expanding the determinant, we get:

$$p(x) = \left(-\frac{25}{3} - x\right)\left(\frac{5}{3} - x\right) - \left(-\frac{43}{6}\right)\left(\frac{43}{6}\right)$$

